LinkedIn-style activity tracking\tab Requires extra services\tab Simpler with Append Blob\tab Azure Blob\par
Conclusion\par
\par
For the three requirements you listed, Azure Blob Storage is the better object storage choice, primarily because of:\par
\par
Blob Index Tags (searchable tags).\par
Append Blob support for profile-view and connection-request activity logs.\par
Equivalent lifecycle management for Hot \f4\u8594?\f1  Cool \f4\u8594?\f1  Archive transitions.\par
\par
However, a LinkedIn-like system should not store actively changing profile/account records directly in object storage. Use a transactional database (e.g., Azure Cosmos DB, Amazon DynamoDB, SQL Server, PostgreSQL) for profile data and use Blob/S3 primarily for:\par
\par
Activity logs\par
Analytics history\par
Profile pictures\par
Resume uploads\par
Archived inactive accounts\par
Data lake storage for reporting and ML workloads.\lang9\par
